==Awards==
In 1983, Vargas received the "Premio Nacional de Periodismo" (National Journalism Prize) in the field of Popular Traditions.<ref name=eluniversal052510/><ref name=googletranslateEluniversal052510/><ref name=conacultagobmx052610/><ref name=googletranslateConacultagobmx052610/> In 2003, the "Premio Nacional de Ciencias y Artes en el <U+00E1>rea de Tradiciones Populares" (National Sciences and Arts Prize) was presented to him.<ref name=eluniversal052510/><ref name=googletranslateEluniversal052510/><ref name=conacultagobmx052610/><ref name=googletranslateConacultagobmx052610/> In 2007, the [[Federal District (Mexico)|Federal District]] government recognized Vargas as a Distinguished Citizen.<ref name=eluniversal052510/> <ref name=googletranslateEluniversal052510/><ref name=conacultagobmx052610/><ref name=googletranslateConacultagobmx052610/> In addition, the Estanquillo Museum Collections exhibited many of his painted works as a [[homage]].<ref name=conacultagobmx052610/><ref name=googletranslateConacultagobmx052610/> At the time of his death, a complete [[exhibition]] of ''La Familia Burr<U+00F3>n'' was on display at a [[museum]] in [[Florence|Florence, Italy]].<ref name=eluniversal052510/><ref name=googletranslateEluniversal052510/>

